{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd84ba0e94a3c4025d24", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "The electric field of an electromagnetic wave in free space is represented as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>E</mi><mo>\u2192</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>\u03c9</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>. The corresponding magnetic induction vector will be :", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "gLaNW", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>\u2192</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>C</mi><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>\u03c9</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "zUg41", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>\u2192</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>C</mi></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>\u03c9</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "Y30cb", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>\u2192</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>C</mi><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>\u03c9</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "in5ne", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>\u2192</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>C</mi></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>\u03c9</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>Given\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>E</mi><mo>\u2192</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>\u03c9</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>:</p><p>Clearly,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>\u03c9</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>)</mo></math>\u00a0term\u00a0represents, electromagnetic wave is travelling along\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mi>z</mi></math>\u00a0direction or along <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>.</p><p>Now, in vector form, direction of electromagnetive wave is given by\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>C</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>E</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>\u00d7</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>. Therefore, magnetic field is along\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>.\u00a0</p><p>Also, we know that\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>C</mi></mfrac></math>, where\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math>\u00a0is speed of light.</p><p>Therefore,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>\u2192</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>C</mi></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>\u03c9</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>.<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "concepts": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ53879181", "subject": "Physics", "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba1"], "topics": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "65c4c0c11d30997d3436bb02", "title": "JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "classes": [], "microConcepts": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["622892fd9f7523577cddc56f", "616024349a1ab852c3621f3c", "61602434741e389e3bfe9c28", "61964c90dbd361e84674fcb5", "61602435374ba1acd615152b", "61bb82195b64558bcac5c98d", "61602433079526ff68bf2908", "61964c91fa250eeb00025cd9", "61c0899871fb803161367f9f", "61e7bd75cfe22022f28241f6", "629109eb647e2f0fcf939346", "62962122b0ae2c997a812c36", "629f390b3ea045f798a076c3", "629f3a904e5aa634f7fe6aca", "64eb06c43118f713ecfef0a5", "66d58538a75f05ee8564f558", "67921d6c1d5b5072da5e9af1", "67fdff4f378e1624ea7b69fa", "680920353a10446a207fdf58"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}